author: By     Victor Reklaitis
title: Suitcase found near possible MH370 debris: reports
text: The remnants of a damaged suitcase have been found near plane debris that's being examined to see if it's linked to missing Malaysia Airlines flight MH370, according to multiple reports Thursday. The debris was discovered on the French island of Réunion near Madagascar. A journalist for a local paper, Journal de L'île de la Réunion, reported what appears to be a suitcase has been found on the Indian Ocean island, less than a day after islanders discovered a two-meter long piece of debris, according to a Sydney Morning Herald article .
